  "text": "In the current implementation of Infnote, in direct connect mode, the servers (full nodes) can provide comprehensive services to clients (light nodes) and access to content that is on the blockchain. However, the servers can feed the clients with wrong information that may not have been written to the blockchain at all. In future work, we plan to update the architecture to use authenticated data structures (ADS) where responders need to also send back proof that the content came from the blockchain it claims [CITATION_1] .",
